import java.io.*;  // Import required classes, such as IOException in case of input/output errors or socket not found exceptions if we use Socket later down the line (TCP and UDP)... etc.. which are imported by default when you write "Import".  
                // Note: Java's I/O utilities have been moved to java.io.* package in version 14 as they were more efficient, safer alternatives for handling input-output operations with sockets during the networked applications of today... etc.. which are imported by default when you write "Import".  
import java.net.*; // Import required classes such as InetAddress and ServerSocket (TCP) or DatagramSocket(UDP). 
                  // Note: Java's Network interfaces have been moved to the new package named 'java.net.*', which are more efficient, safer alternatives for handling network-related operations with sockets during today... etc.. then these classes would be imported by default when you write "Import".  
import javax.crypto.*; // Import cryptographic tools from Java Cryptography Architecture (JCA)  - Bouncy Castle has been used in this example because it's widely accepted and easy to use for all your needs... etc.. which are not needed here as we only need basic socket programming, so I have commented out them.